Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery vessel, perhaps a large oinochoe; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between buff to reddish brown margins, with numerous mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Perhaps from same vessel as 1888,0601.618; certainly from same pot as 1965,030.427.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.090)
